priciples
    Defense in Depth: Implementing multiple layers of security controls to protect 
        against various types of threats.
    Least Privilege: Granting users and systems only the minimum level of access
    separation of Duties: Dividing responsibilities among different individuals or systems
         to reduce the risk of insider threats and errors.
    security by design: Integrating security considerations into the design and development
        of systems and applications from the outset.
    KISS: Keep It Simple, Stupid: Designing security measures that are straightforward and easy to understand
    Security by obscurity: Relying on secrecy to protect systems and data, which is generally considered a weak security approach.
    
CIA architecture:
    Confidentiality: Ensuring that sensitive information is only accessible to authorized individuals or systems.
    Integrity: Maintaining the accuracy and consistency of data and systems, preventing unauthorized modifications. logging everything, if someone modifies or tempers, if we are aware of it
    Availability: Ensuring that systems and data are accessible and usable when needed, minimizing downtime and disruptions.